# Template — copy the KEY names below into .env; set real (encrypted) values via dotenvx.
# Do NOT put real secrets here (this file is committed). Every value here stays blank.
#
# HOW TO GENERATE / FIND EACH VALUE (dashboard URLs, exact CLI, secret-or-not, rotation):
#   → .claude/skills/wire-supabase-feature/credentials.md   (the per-credential reference)
#
# The set flow (paste → encrypt → back up the private key):
#   make collect-secret VARS="PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY"  # seed + open .env
#   # paste each value next to NAME=, then:
#   make encrypt        # plaintext → dotenvx `encrypted:` ciphertext (safe to commit)
#   make key-backup     # back .env.keys up to LastPass (survives a fresh clone)
# Run a command with the decrypted env (how deploy:internal auths):
#   ./node_modules/.bin/dotenvx run -- wrangler pages deploy ...

# Deploy-time only (SECRET). Cloudflare Pages:Edit scoped token. See credentials.md.
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=

# Comment layer (internal build only). Both PUBLISHABLE — not secret; RLS is the enforcer.
# See credentials.md for where to get them (Supabase MCP get_project_url / get_publishable_keys).
PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# NOTE: the ES256 signing key is NOT an env var here. Prod = a wrangler pages secret;
# local dev = symlink .signing-key.jwk.json to the shared gtm key. See credentials.md +
# `make signing-key-status`.
